Problem statement: Right now, for all paginated searches, we set the sort filter on  createdDate . However, when the user applies sorting on another field from the UI (default is  paymentDueDate ), sorting is applied to both fields, making the query inefficient. We excluded all date filters from this condition, but we should also exclude any filter which has a unique field. Query: {"deleted":false,"unitId":"160","accessibleByAP":true,"userId":{"$in":["78726"]}},"sort":{"invoiceNumber":1,"createdDate":1} Code: com.vroozi.api.common.filter.PageFilter#buildPageable   static Pageable buildPageable(
      Integer pageSize, Integer currentPage, String sortField, Sort.Direction sortOrder
  ) {
    Sort.Direction direction = isNull(sortOrder) ? Sort.Direction.DESC : sortOrder;
    sortField = isNullOrEmpty(sortField) ? CommonFields.CREATED_DATE : sortField;
    List<Sort.Order> sortOrders = new LinkedList<>();
    sortOrders.add(new Sort.Order(direction, sortField));
    if (!DATE_FILTERS.contains(sortField)) {
      // To make sure fields with repeated values are always sorted in the same order we add this even if a sort field was provided (except for date fields)
      sortOrders.add(new Sort.Order(direction, CommonFields.CREATED_DATE));
    }
    return PageRequest.of(currentPage - 1, pageSize, Sort.by(sortOrders));
  } Suggested Change: Need to remove the default sort on  CREATED_DATE  if user filter bases on invoiceNumber field as well. (For now we’ll only do invoice number, so impact is not big, but we’ll add the rest of the unique fields in ticket   )

See related ticket for more information:    When doing a user search (with a text search), and when SDM is enabled we are also finding users matching the text with their production name. This is the code:     if (!requestDTO.isSupplierUsersOnly() && isSDMFeatureEnabled
        && isSDMOrNoRoleFilter(requestDTO)) {
      // FIXME: This code looks wrong, and probably should be done differently, but we don't know where it's being used from or why it was added
      requestDTO.setUserIds(productionService
          .findDistinctUserByProductionName(requestDTO.getUnitId(), requestDTO.getSearchText(),
              requestDTO.getActiveProduction()));
    } And then when doing the filter into the DB we are adding them with an OR:     if (CollectionUtils.isNotEmpty(requestDTO.getUserIds())) {
      criteria =
          new Criteria()
              .orOperator(criteria, where(UNIT_ID).in(requestDTO.getUnitId()).and(DELETED).is(false)
                  .and(USER_ID).in(requestDTO.getUserIds()));
    } The issue is that the DB filter is not considering the rest of the parameters in  FindUserRequestDTO  , so it could show, for example, inactive users, or could be showing the userIDsToExclude. We need to fix this code so that all parameters are considered.

