Business Case: The system should allow users to enable or disable feature flags for  External Workflow ,  External Accounting Validation , or both as needed. Acceptance Criteria: The  Company Settings  collection currently contains a single flag for  External Workflow  and  External Accounting Validation.  The feature flag of these two functionalities should be segregated. This should allow the admins to configure whichever external service they require. Please review the technical details section for all the potential texting scenarios after this implementation. Technical Details: We are using the externalFlowEnalbed flag in company settings to determine if the internal or external service for (accounting validation, timeline preview etc). This flag is not enough for handling mix of use cases where one service is using internal workflow and other using the external workflow. We need to introduce new setting in company_settings, that can be used to determine if the external services are enabled and than we need to check for individual services like accounting validation and workflow time line to be enabled for external or internal workflow. We need to introduce new externalSericeConfigurations in companySettings that will have following details.     "externalServiceConfiguration" : {
           "accountingValidation":boolean,
           "timeline": boolean
           } Based on this setting we need to update both FE and BE to use these flags. Possible use cases to consider: 0: Any one of them is configured, only that will execute 1- both internal 2 - both external 3- accounting external (USJ) and timeline internal 4- accounting external (USJ) and timeline external (NBCU) 5- accounting external (USJ) and timeline external (NEW) 6- accounting external (NEW) and timeline internal 7- accounting external (NEW) and timeline external (NBCU) 8- accounting external (NEW) and timeline external (NEW) 9- accounting internal and timeline external (NBCU) 10- accounting internal and timeline external (NEW) Pre-Condition: External Approval Workflow is configured on the devqa2 server. Steps to reproduce: Server : DEVQA2  PMan DevQA2 Login : masood.safi+ employee@vroozi.com Password : Welcome1! Navigate to the Purchase Requests - Go to the Pending screen and create new PR . Provide all mandatory fields. Click on the Submit Button. PR should be submitted. Actual Result: Following Error is displayed 404 : "HTTP Status 404 – Not Found HTTP Status 404 – Not Found Type  Status Report Message  The requested resource [/integrationapi/api/mock/nbcu/pr/submit/action/create] is not available Description  The origin server did not find a current representation for the target resource or is not willing to disclose that one exists. Apache Tomcat/9.0.68 Expected Result: PR should be submitted without error

